G∙D Does Great Kindness To Us Each Day. He gives us life, food, air,
shelter & clothes. G∙d gave Jews His Law, the Torah at Sinai, that provides 7
Laws for all Humanity, for a peaceful world. Only once in History did a Nation
of millions of people hear G∙d & witness the giving of a Divine Law – when
G∙d gave the Torah to the Jews. It has not changed. Moses taught detail.
G∙d’s Existence is Evident by observing the order & beauty of nature. It
testifies to a Creator. G∙d / Hash∙m* is One, Omniscient, changes not His
mind & has no body.
To Receive a Place in Heaven, one accepts Torah as G∙d's true Law. A Jew
observes Jewish Law / Shulchan Aruch. A Gentile observes Laws of Noah
stated in Torah & thus receives title of Ben Noah’ / Child of Noah! Learning
one’s laws enables us to be refined, kind & wise. We discover meaning, the
purpose of & our purpose in life & our potential in perfecting the world. We
learn how to be good in G∙d’s eyes, ways of self-improvement & how to have
a relationship with Him. Everyone can improve & be good. G∙d Loves Those
Who Keep His Laws.
